            . I am a <rs id="t18230910-292-viclabel1567" type="occupation">coal meter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-292-victim2549 t18230910-292-viclabel1567"></join>, and live in Lambeth-street. On the 9th of August, I was in <placeName id="t18230910-292-crimeloc1568">Jerusalem-passage, Clerkenwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-292-crimeloc1568" type="placeName" value="Jerusalem-passage, Clerkenwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-292-crimeloc1568" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-292-off1565 t18230910-292-crimeloc1568"></join>, between twelve and one o'clock; somebody spoke to me - I felt and missed my handkerchief; the person pointed to the prisoner; I seized him, he denied taking it. I took him to a constable, who searched him, but could not find it; it was a large blue one, with white spots.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-292-person2551">
                  JOHN 
                  BRYAN
               <interp inst="t18230910-292-person2551" type="surname" value="BRYAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-292-person2551" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-292-person2551" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a lapidary, and was in Jerusalem passage, and saw the prisoner with another young man behind Riley; I saw the prisoner put his hand into Riley's pocket, and pull out a large blue silk handkerchief - he was about twenty yards from me; he gave it to his companion, who ran off with it immediately. I told Riley, he secured the prisoner, but the other got away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-292-person2552">
                  JOHN 
                  BALLARD
               <interp inst="t18230910-292-person2552" type="surname" value="BALLARD"></interp>
